race.description: Barmah Park Restaurant & Cellar Door Maiden Plate
race.comment: KALIZMA (10) started $4 last time and ran below expectations, finishing fifth and beaten 5 lengths at Geelong over 1107m. Finds an easier assignment than starts to date, at peak fitness now and drawn nicely. PRESTIGE ZERPRISE (6) finished out of the money on debut two starts back then was beaten 6 lengths when fourth over 1115m at Kyneton 2.5 weeks ago. Finds a nice race and can figure in the finish. DUBAI ADVENTURE (4) is the best-bred horse in the race, by gun stallion Street Boss out of Magic Millions winner Exhilarates, who has a shocking gate but went well in a recent jumpout alongside Alphabet, who runs in R2, which could prove a good guide to his chances. KADESH (16) is another first-starter from a powerful stable and has looked good at the jumpouts of late, including a nice win at Pakenham at her latest.
